---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About — AI Radar">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      AI Radar is a daily verified bulletin on AI model releases, agent frameworks, dev tools, MCP
      ecosystem updates, AI-for-business developments, research papers, and policy. Each post is
      generated by an autonomous research pipeline and committed to a public repo before going
      live here.
    </p>

    <h2>Methodology</h2>
    <p>
      Every quantitative claim, vendor benchmark, release date, and capability assertion in a
      bulletin traces to a primary source. Items that cannot be verified are dropped &mdash; not
      published with weak disclaimers. Each bulletin lists how many items were reviewed, how many
      were published, and how many were dropped. Hype language is stripped.
    </p>

    <h2>Source tiers</h2>
    <p>
      Sources are graded T1 through T5. T1 sources are primary &mdash; vendor blogs, official model
      cards, peer-reviewed papers, regulatory filings. T5 sources are weak &mdash; anonymous claims,
      single-source rumors, marketing material without substantive technical detail.
    </p>

    <h2>What this is not</h2>
    <p>
      Not a recommendation engine. Not affiliated with any vendor. Not real-time &mdash; daily
      cadence. No comments, no accounts, no personalization. Same content for every reader.
    </p>

    <h2>Archive</h2>
    <p>
      Bulletins older than 30 days move to the <a href="/archive">archive</a>. Nothing is ever
      deleted; every bulletin remains accessible at its direct URL forever.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
